# Cursor workspace

Canonical architecture and invariants: root `AGENTS.md` (shared with OpenCode). Scoped rules below add file-targeted checklists; they do not replace `AGENTS.md`.

## When to read which doc

| Task | Start here |
|------|------------|
| Architecture / contracts | `AGENTS.md` |
| Local dev & `.venv` | `README.md` → Develop |
| Tests on a new machine | `docs/development/TESTING.md` |
| Packaging / installers | `docs/development/BUILD_INSTRUCTIONS.md` |
| Recorder stdout JSON | `docs/features/json-based-events.md` + `.cursor/rules/recorder-stdout-contract.mdc` |
| AI catalog pins | `docs/development/LOCAL_AI_MODEL_CATALOG.md` + `.cursor/rules/local-ai-addons.mdc` |
| macOS capture (shipped vs planned) | `docs/features/MACOS_AUDIO_ARCHITECTURE.md` |
| Manual recorder QA | `tests/manual/recording-smoke-checklist.md` |
| Manual AI add-ons QA | `tests/manual/local-ai-addons-checklist.md` |

## Commands (repo root)

```bash
npm start | npm run dev
npm test              # JS helpers + syntax (--check main, preload, app, history-detail-helpers)
npm run test:python
npm run test:all      # before PRs
npm run prepare-build # before packaged builds
```

Windows: `py -3.11`; macOS: `python3.11`. Dev Python: repo `.venv` (auto-detected) or `AVANEVIS_PYTHON`.

## Scoped rules (`.cursor/rules/`)

| Rule | Triggers on |
|------|-------------|
| `recorder-stdout-contract` | Recorders, `src/main.js`, main-process helpers |
| `electron-ipc` | Main, preload, renderer |
| `transcription-model-cache` | Transcription cache / Whisper spawn env |
| `local-ai-addons` | AI add-on catalog, diarization, summaries |
| `meeting-metadata` | `meeting_manager.py` |
| `macos-swift-helper` | Swift helper + macOS recorder bridge |
| `renderer-patterns` | Renderer UI and helper modules |
| `python-backend` | `backend/**` |
| `build-packaging` | Build scripts, `package.json`, updater |
| `validation-and-ci` | `tests/**`, workflows |

## Agent maintenance

- After JS helper or Python backend changes: run `npm test` and `npm run test:python` when relevant.
- Update `AGENTS.md` when changing cross-process contracts, AI catalog pins, build inputs, or validation expectations.
- Do not add repo-root `CLAUDE.md` (duplicates context with `AGENTS.md`).
